profile_positions.description:
Joolz is a Dutch company from Amsterdam (founded in 2004) that designs and manufactures ergonomic pushchairs and accessories. Designed around the needs of the human body of both parent and child. Our goal is to inspire young families to live a positive life; from pregnancy to the first day at school. We call this Positive Design. This is reflected in our award-winning ergonomic products, re-usable packaging, Birth Forest, the partners with whom we work and the steps we take in the area of sustainability. Currently, Joolz is available in 29 countries (and counting) in Europe, Asia, Australia, and the United States.
joolz.com

As Creative Brand & Art Director responsible for:
- the vision, positioning, identity, concept and art direction according to the brand values;
- ensuring that all brand messages across all touchpoints are consistent and in line with the brand values and image (i.e. look and feel and tone of voice); 
- creation and execution of innovative and creative concepts for brand and sales campaigns for all B2C and B2B omnichannel touchpoints (including videography, photography, content production, styling, graphic design, tone-of-voice); 
- product concepts and design, working together with the product department; 
- partnering with the e-commerce and marketing team to ensure an optimal online customer experience (on- and offsite) that fits the brand standards; 
- the design of the shop-in-shops around the world and the interior design of the recurring B2B and B2C fairs together with the 2D and 3D designer in-house; 
- management of the in-house creative team and external agencies (graphic designers, copywriters, digital A/V editors, 2D and 3D designer, front-end developers, animation designers, stand and construction builders); 
- inspiring and mentoring the team to stimulate growth and personal development based on company and personal KPI’s; 
- continuously inspiring, raising the bar and challenging the company on a visionary and creative level.

‘Let’s make things more beautiful’. That is the mission of Het Hoofdbureau. Founded 21 years ago and with an office in the heart of Amsterdam for over 15 years. Het Hoofdbureau is a communication, photography and design-focused consultancy agency working amongst other brands for Novotel Amsterdam City, Shell, Nauta Dutilh, Tefaf, Leica, BAM, Unique Uitzendbureau, Nederlandse Orde van Advocaten, Marcel Wolterinck.
hoofdbureau.com

Main responsible for concept, development, and execution of creative concepts for leading-edge marketing, branding, graphic, interior design, photography and design solutions.

- communicate with senior management of clients and stakeholders to develop an aesthetic and brand that reflects the company’s core brand values and ideals; 
- managing and delegating projects to the internal and external teams with different disciplines (strategy, copy, art, project managers);
- reviewing the graphic materials of the teams to assess their validity based on the clients brand brief and maintain graphic consistency;
- directing, inspiring and motivating internal and external creatives and designers;
- mentoring junior staff in project development and performance management based on company and personal KPI’s;
- initiating, organizing and leading brainstorming sessions for clients as well as for the in-house team, and ensure a decent follow-up.

Responsible for executing concepts and brand guidelines for several multinationals 
and other clients.

Responsible for:
conceiving, developing and delivering high-quality design concepts based on research and a good understanding of clients’ needs;
design integration and adaptation of new brand guidelines throughout all touchpoints;
presenting ideas and concepts to stakeholders, both internal and external;
(re)develop branding standards and visions according to guidelines;
working together with project managers and a team of creatives.

The Temperament Magazine (nowadays known as The Espanja Magazine) is a wonderfully inspiring magazine about Spain, the Spanish language and culture and travelling in Spain.

As graphic designer responsible for the rebranding of the magazine; generate a new brand philosophy and identity and layout the issues.

developing excellence through innovative & creative artwork for the magazine itself 
and across all media;
rebranding and redesign of an existing magazine and all it’s media adaptations;
working with a team of dedicated partners of the magazine to bring themes to life;
ability to work with project managers and a team of creatives.
